	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="2" facs="R 6456-39 (41)"/>
			<p>But, as earlier despatches have already suggested, the lot of the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-896"
					type="subject">Jews</term> in <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/798549/romania.html">Rumania</placeName> has definitely
				worsened since the inauguration of the <orgName ref="#ehri_dr_government_rumanian">present regime</orgName> three months ago. In the
				first place, the green-shirted <ref target="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities?q=Iron+Guard">Iron Guard</ref> is in power, and
				the <ref target="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities?q=Iron+Guard">Iron Guard</ref> is notoriously and avowedly an essentially
					<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-352" type="subject">anti-Semitic organization</term>. <pb n="3"
					facs="R 6456-39 (42)"/> In the second place, <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/798549/romania.html">Rumania</placeName> not
				only has come under the direct ‘influence’ of <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1159" type="subject">Nazi
					Germany</term> but is now actually a member of the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1027"
					type="subject">Axis</term> and an adherent to the <ref target="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tripartite_Pact">Tripartite
					Pact</ref>. And, thirdly, the country requires scape-goats for all the evils and misfortunes of the day, and finds that the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-896" type="subject">Jews</term>, along with former <persName
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_pers-001424">King Carol</persName> and the old politicians, serve admirably
				in this unhappy role. These considerations, plus an underlying sentiment of genuine <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-329" type="subject">anti-Semitism</term> generally, provide sufficient
				reason and background for <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-896" type="subject">Jewish</term>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-829" type="subject">fears</term> and sufferings in <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/798549/romania.html">Rumania</placeName> today. [...]</p>
			<pb n="5" facs="R 6456-39 (44)"/>
			<p>In recent weeks the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-896" type="subject">Jewish</term> plaint has not been
				one of lost positions, special <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1047" type="subject">taxes</term> or
					<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-332" type="subject">discriminatory restrictions</term> – that is an
				old story. Rather it has been one of <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-536" type="subject">deaths</term>,
					<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-562" type="subject">torture</term>, beatings, <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-636" type="subject">abductions</term>, <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-584" type="subject">confiscation</term>, <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-660" type="subject">robbery</term> and <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-345" type="subject">violence</term> in all forms. It is not an
				exaggeration to say that here today one sees the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-896" type="subject"
					>Jews</term> with tears, hollow eyes and wringing hands. Many of them never go out; they keep to their homes for <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-829" type="subject">fear</term> of meeting <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-345" type="subject">violence</term> in the street. A few, who have reasons
				to <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-829" type="subject">fear</term> they may be sought out, creep from
				friend to friend or house to house afraid to go to their own homes to sleep. Those of means endeavor frantically to dispose of their
					<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-945" type="subject">property</term>, secure funds abroad and find a
				way to <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-203" type="subject">leave the country</term>.</p>
